But I

565
00:23:43,580 --> 00:23:45,900
still don't want you to move elsewhere.

566
00:23:48,220 --> 00:23:49,060
Don't worry.

567
00:23:49,580 --> 00:23:51,140
I've thought about it.

568
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:53,500
I've specially reserved

569
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:55,820
a room for you in this new house.

570
00:23:56,060 --> 00:23:56,980
It's right here.

571
00:23:56,980 --> 00:23:58,620
After we really move to the new house,

572
00:23:58,620 --> 00:24:00,420
you can come to visit us anytime.

573
00:24:03,980 --> 00:24:04,900
Godfather,

574
00:24:05,220 --> 00:24:08,340
why don't you talk to Ling Chao patiently again?

575
00:24:08,940 --> 00:24:11,200
Or you can take him to the villa directly.

576
00:24:11,780 --> 00:24:13,300
Then he might agree.

577
00:24:15,260 --> 00:24:15,850
Okay.

578
00:24:16,140 --> 00:24:17,020
I'll carefully discuss it

579
00:24:17,020 --> 00:24:18,550
with your godmother again.

580
00:24:30,620 --> 00:24:31,460
I'm the elder sister.

581
00:24:31,460 --> 00:24:33,340
I never lie to little brothers.

582
00:24:33,340 --> 00:24:34,220
If you don't believe me,

583
00:24:34,220 --> 00:24:36,620
I'll wait for my godfather with you.

584
00:24:37,580 --> 00:24:39,260
My doll and I will always be with you

585
00:24:39,260 --> 00:24:40,300
and protect you.

586
00:24:40,300 --> 00:24:41,780
Thank you, Sister.

587
00:24:56,370 --> 00:24:57,210
Who is it?

588
00:25:00,420 --> 00:25:01,460
Ling Chao.

589
00:25:01,780 --> 00:25:04,020
Are you really going to move to a new house?

590
00:25:04,020 --> 00:25:04,820
If you wake me up

591
00:25:04,820 --> 00:25:06,060
at 6 a.m. again

592
00:25:06,060 --> 00:25:07,290
next time,

593
00:25:07,290 --> 00:25:08,580
I'd rather move elsewhere.

594
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:10,710
Then I won't wake you up so early again.

595
00:25:17,100 --> 00:25:17,700
You...

596
00:25:18,410 --> 00:25:20,670
How come you have no sense of humor at all?

597
00:25:21,460 --> 00:25:22,780
I'm just kidding.

598
00:25:23,340 --> 00:25:24,940
It has nothing to do with you.

599
00:25:26,660 --> 00:25:27,700
I know that

600
00:25:27,820 --> 00:25:29,500
you don't lack anything in your new house,

601
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:31,780
but you still need to take some things with you.

602
00:25:31,780 --> 00:25:32,840
For this tea table,

603
00:25:32,900 --> 00:25:35,210
we scrambled for candies here when we were kids,

604
00:25:35,210 --> 00:25:36,700
which made you hurt your head.

605
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:39,030
You still have a scar on your forehead now.

606
00:25:39,500 --> 00:25:40,900
And this cabinet.

607
00:25:41,580 --> 00:25:43,900
We played hide-and-seek here when we were kids.

608
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:44,940
You hid inside.

609
00:25:45,020 --> 00:25:46,420
In the middle of the game,

610
00:25:46,420 --> 00:25:47,860
I was attracted by the sugar cakes

611
00:25:47,860 --> 00:25:48,980
bought by my godmother.

612
00:25:48,980 --> 00:25:50,820
Because of that, you hid inside for a long time,

613
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:52,280
and fell asleep in the end.

614
00:25:53,540 --> 00:25:54,730
And this sofa.

615
00:25:55,260 --> 00:25:56,500
When we were in junior high school,

616
00:25:56,500 --> 00:25:57,940
we sat here and ate watermelon.

617
00:25:57,940 --> 00:25:59,660
We insisted on having a competition of spitting watermelon seeds.

618
00:25:59,660 --> 00:26:02,260
But we had to clean them by ourselves in the end.

619
00:26:02,290 --> 00:26:04,820
Now that I think of it, we were quite childish.

620
00:26:04,980 --> 00:26:06,420
And that little turtle.

621
00:26:06,740 --> 00:26:08,220
You must take it with you.

622
00:26:08,420 --> 00:26:10,460
Otherwise, it will starve to death.

623
00:26:12,220 --> 00:26:13,580
Did you skip breakfast?

624
00:26:14,100 --> 00:26:15,620
Why do you sound so weak when you talk?

625
00:26:15,620 --> 00:26:16,980
At this time,

626
00:26:16,980 --> 00:26:18,710
how could I have the mood to eat?

627
00:26:20,020 --> 00:26:21,660
Porridge or deep-fried dough sticks?

628
00:26:21,660 --> 00:26:25,660
Of course I'll eat Madam Zhang's soy milk with deep-fried dough sticks.

629
00:26:30,020 --> 00:26:31,740
When these dough sticks were fried,

630
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:33,540
the temperature of the oil was just appropriate.

631
00:26:33,540 --> 00:26:35,270
Both sides look golden yellow.

632
00:26:35,340 --> 00:26:37,180
It tastes crispy outside but tender inside.

633
00:26:37,180 --> 00:26:39,820
Take a sip of sweet soy milk while eating it.

634
00:26:39,900 --> 00:26:41,180
It's chewy

635
00:26:41,070 --> 00:26:44,870
[Nutritious Breakfast]

636
00:26:41,180 --> 00:26:42,980
with different layers of taste.

637
00:26:52,540 --> 00:26:53,500
When we eat steamed buns,

638
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:55,020
we should eat them with this dipping sauce.

639
00:26:55,020 --> 00:26:56,140
It tastes sweet and sour.

640
00:26:56,140 --> 00:26:59,140
It's also appetizing and helps to cleanse the palate.

641
00:26:59,260 --> 00:27:00,010
Ling Chao.

642
00:27:00,780 --> 00:27:03,220
There are so many delicious foods for breakfast.

643
00:27:03,220 --> 00:27:05,550
Are you really willing to move elsewhere?

644
00:27:12,410 --> 00:27:13,380
Hey!

645
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:14,340
I've told you so much.

646
00:27:14,340 --> 00:27:15,420
Did you hear me?

647
00:27:17,700 --> 00:27:19,760
Who said that I would move elsewhere?

648
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:21,950
Don't worry.

649
00:27:25,220 --> 00:27:26,020
I won't leave.

650
00:27:31,500 --> 00:27:32,260
Eat more.

651
00:27:32,260 --> 00:27:33,810
Come on. Eat more. Just eat.

652
00:27:34,620 --> 00:27:35,290
Eat more.

653
00:27:35,460 --> 00:27:36,300
Eat more.

654
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:36,980
This is delicious.

655
00:27:36,980 --> 00:27:37,740
It's very delicious.

656
00:27:37,740 --> 00:27:38,940
This is also delicious.

657
00:27:38,940 --> 00:27:39,820
This is yours, too.

658
00:27:39,820 --> 00:27:40,880
They're all yours.

659
00:27:40,980 --> 00:27:42,010
Eat. Just eat.

660
00:27:52,220 --> 00:27:53,420
Where did Ling Chao

661
00:27:53,420 --> 00:27:55,180
go so early in the morning?

662
00:27:56,020 --> 00:27:56,980
He even didn't bring his mobile phone with him.

663
00:27:56,980 --> 00:27:58,620
I wonder if he had breakfast.

664
00:27:58,900 --> 00:27:59,960
Leave some for him.

665
00:28:04,340 --> 00:28:05,300
Look at this bowl.

666
00:28:05,300 --> 00:28:06,980
Chao refused to eat when he was a kid.

667
00:28:06,980 --> 00:28:08,840
He even broke a corner of the bowl.

668
00:28:09,180 --> 00:28:10,140
I didn't expect that he would use

669
00:28:10,140 --> 00:28:11,060
this small broken bowl

670
00:28:11,060 --> 00:28:12,380
for so many years.

671
00:28:14,820 --> 00:28:15,540
Ling,

672
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:18,960
are we really going to move to a new house?

673
00:28:22,380 --> 00:28:23,260
You're back.

674
00:28:23,620 --> 00:28:25,820
Where did you go so early in the morning?

675
00:28:25,860 --> 00:28:27,260
I bought some breakfast.

676
00:28:27,570 --> 00:28:28,980
You went to buy the breakfast.

677
00:28:28,980 --> 00:28:29,660
Let's eat together.

678
00:28:29,660 --> 00:28:30,740
I'll fetch a bowl for you.

679
00:28:30,740 --> 00:28:31,330
Okay.

680
00:28:37,940 --> 00:28:38,740
Come on. Here.

681
00:28:42,180 --> 00:28:43,980
Why did you get up so early today?

682
00:28:58,540 --> 00:28:59,670
Put it in the middle.

683
00:28:59,980 --> 00:29:02,860
Why did you think of buying deep-fried dough sticks today?

684
00:29:02,860 --> 00:29:03,860
I just went out

685
00:29:03,890 --> 00:29:05,140
and happened to see them, so...

686
00:29:05,140 --> 00:29:06,940
Is it because I like eating them?

687
00:29:07,700 --> 00:29:08,500
We won't move.

688
00:29:17,060 --> 00:29:18,390
We're not going to move.

689
00:29:33,740 --> 00:29:34,780
Come on. Let's eat.

690
00:29:34,780 --> 00:29:35,420
Okay.

691
00:29:51,580 --> 00:29:52,840
The books are all here.

692
00:29:53,380 --> 00:29:54,900
See if there's any book you're looking for.

693
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:56,630
Then I won't stand on ceremony.

694
00:30:05,410 --> 00:30:07,700
There are so many books about the major of Computer Science.

695
00:30:07,700 --> 00:30:10,620
Are you going to apply for the major of Computer Science in the future?

696
00:30:10,620 --> 00:30:11,900
I bought them because I was interested.

697
00:30:11,900 --> 00:30:13,780
I think you are talented in this.

698
00:30:13,860 --> 00:30:15,050
Why don't you consider

699
00:30:15,050 --> 00:30:16,180
joining my company?

700
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:19,120
